{"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","modules":[{"name":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall"}],"role":"article","title":"Platform Behavior"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/PlatformBehavior","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall\/platformbehavior"]}],"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"Why the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"revenueCatPaywall"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"revenueCatCustomerCenter"},{"type":"text","text":" modifiers present differently on iOS and macOS, and what is hard-coded."}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"anchor":"Related-Documentation","title":"Related Documentation","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToPresentTheUI"],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywallUI","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" documentation provides the matching API reference for the modifiers described here.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Explanation","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/EntitlementMapping"],"generated":true,"title":"Explanation"}],"kind":"article","schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The bundled UI is intentionally opinionated. Each modifier picks the platform-appropriate presentation so consumers don’t have to repeat the conditional compilation themselves, and so the dispatch flow stays symmetric across platforms — the same "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".paywall(.dismiss)"},{"type":"text","text":" action fires from a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fullScreenCover"},{"text":" on iOS and from a sheet on macOS.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This article explains the reasoning behind those choices and what is fixed versus configurable.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"revenueCatPaywall","level":2,"anchor":"revenueCatPaywall","type":"heading"},{"header":"row","type":"table","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Platform","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Presentation","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Reason","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"iOS"}]}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"fullScreenCover","type":"codeVoice"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A subscription paywall is a primary moment, not an interrupt. "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fullScreenCover"},{"text":" keeps the UI immersive, prevents accidental gesture-dismiss, and matches App Store conventions.","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"macOS","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"sheet","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"frame(minWidth: 400, minHeight: 600)"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Mac sheets do not expand to fill the parent window. Without an explicit minimum size the paywall would render too small to legibly show plan options. The 400×600 minimum is roughly the size RevenueCatUI’s templates assume.","type":"text"}]}]]]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The minimum frame is hard-coded; it is not exposed as a parameter. If your paywall layout needs more room on macOS, wrap the modified view in a parent that imposes a larger frame, or use ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RevenueCatUI.PaywallView"},{"text":" directly inside a custom ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"sheet"},{"text":" modifier.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"revenueCatCustomerCenter","level":2,"anchor":"revenueCatCustomerCenter","type":"heading"},{"type":"table","rows":[[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Platform"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Presentation","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Reason","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"iOS"}]}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"sheet"},{"text":" with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RevenueCatUI.CustomerCenterView"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"RevenueCatUI ships a customer center on iOS only. A non-fullscreen ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"sheet"},{"text":" is appropriate because customer-center actions are administrative, not part of a purchase flow.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"macOS"}]}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Opens ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"itms-apps:\/\/apps.apple.com\/account\/subscriptions"},{"text":" and immediately fires ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"onDismiss"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"RevenueCatUI does not ship a customer center on macOS, and the system has no equivalent in-app surface. The App Store subscription management page is what users expect on the Mac, so the sheet hands off to it and clears its own presentation state immediately.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]]],"header":"row"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The macOS branch clears the binding and fires "},{"code":"onDismiss","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" synchronously after "},{"code":"NSWorkspace.shared.open","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" so "},{"code":"PaywallState.isCustomerCenterPresented","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" does not get stuck "},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". The user returns from App Store to find the app’s UI in its idle state."}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Why-no-platform-override-hooks","level":2,"text":"Why no platform-override hooks"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Both modifiers are deliberately parameter-light: an "},{"code":"isPresented: Binding<Bool>","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and an optional "},{"code":"onDismiss: () -> Void","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". There is no "},{"code":"paywallStyle:","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"code":"presentationKind:","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" parameter."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The reasoning: any consumer that needs to deviate from the chosen presentation already has the underlying RevenueCatUI types ("},{"code":"PaywallView","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"CustomerCenterView","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":") and SwiftUI’s full presentation surface ("},{"code":"sheet","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"fullScreenCover","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"popover","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", custom containers). The bundled modifiers exist to handle the 95% case in one line — when the 5% case applies, drop down to RevenueCatUI directly."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This package does not try to be the complete paywall-UI library. It is the "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"integration layer","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" that makes the common case trivial."}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"What-is-configurable","level":2,"text":"What is configurable"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The configurable surface lives in "},{"code":"RevenueCatUI","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and on the paywall plugin:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Paywall content, copy, and template","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — configured in the RevenueCat dashboard. "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RevenueCatUI.PaywallView"},{"type":"text","text":" renders whichever offering and template the dashboard returns."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Customer-center labels, sections, and actions","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — configured in the RevenueCat dashboard. "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RevenueCatUI.CustomerCenterView"},{"type":"text","text":" renders whichever configuration the dashboard returns."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Presentation triggering","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — driven by the plugin via "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallState.isPresented"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isCustomerCenterPresented"},{"type":"text","text":". Your code chooses "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"when","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" to set them via "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".request(reason:)"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".presentCustomerCenter"},{"type":"text","text":" actions."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Dismiss behavior","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — your "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"onDismiss"},{"type":"text","text":" closures dispatch the matching paywall actions. Replace them if you need analytics hooks or cleanup beyond the default flow."}]}]}]}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"doc://SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/documentation/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall","role":"collection","url":"\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall","kind":"symbol","title":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"RevenueCat adapter for Swidux’s "},{"code":"PaywallPlugin","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". Implements "},{"code":"PaywallService","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" against "},{"code":"Purchases.shared","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", ships a controllable mock for previews and tests, and pairs with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywallUI"},{"type":"text","text":" for drop-in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallView"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CustomerCenterView"},{"text":" presentation.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic"},"doc://SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/documentation/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/EntitlementMapping":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/EntitlementMapping","url":"\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall\/entitlementmapping","title":"Entitlement Mapping","kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"How RevenueCat’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CustomerInfo.entitlements"},{"type":"text","text":" translates to Swidux’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"EntitlementSnapshot"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"role":"article","type":"topic"},"doc://SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/documentation/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/HowToPresentTheUI":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToPresentTheUI","url":"\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall\/howtopresenttheui","title":"How to Present the UI","kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Attach the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"revenueCatPaywall"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"revenueCatCustomerCenter"},{"type":"text","text":" view modifiers from "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywallUI"},{"type":"text","text":" to a root view, driven by "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallState"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"role":"article","type":"topic"}}}